
1. The Function Exercise Without Parameters: 

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <title>JavaScript Function Application</title>
        <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            function heyYouTubers() {                           // function without parameter
                document.write("Hey YouTubers!");
            }
        </script>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h3>JavaScript Function Application</h3>
        <form><input type="button" onclick="heyYouTubers()" value="Greet Viewers"></form>
    </body>
</html>

2. The Function Exercise With Parameters:

        <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            function heyYouTubers(subject, score) {
                document.write("The score for " + subject + " is " + score + ", in the last exam.");
            }
        </script>
    </head>
    <body>
        <h3>JavaScript Function Application</h3>
        <form><input type="button" onclick="heyYouTubers('JavaScript', 74)" value="Subject score"></form>
    </body>

3. The Function Exercise With a Return Function:

        <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
            function fullNames(first, last) {
               var names;
                names = first + " " + last;
                return names;
            }
            function returnNames() {
                var answer;
                answer = fullNames('John', 'Juliet');
                document.write("Full Names: " + answer);
            }
        </script>

    <body>
        <h3>JavaScript Function Application</h3>
        <form><input type="button" onclick="returnNames()" value="Give Names"></form>
    </body>
